We’ve been coming regularly and always happy with friendly staff and great food.
We also enjoy their variety of makgeolli from Korea, highly recommended!
Great beer and great meat, the pork collar and l.a galbi are a must try.
Amazing food with good draft beer! Will definitely be back for more
Always a great meal made with quality produce here.  Perilla oil noodles is a must try,

Discovered this spot through a friend, and it really stands out from the usual K-BBQ joints along Tanjong Pagar. The key difference? The quality of the meat. There’s a dedicated counter where you can choose your preferred cuts, and the team grills them to your ideal doneness. They do serve a small selection of noodles, stews, etc.

You can also buy the raw cuts to take home and cook on your own. Bonus points for their curated selection of makgeolli, featuring unique labels you don’t typically see elsewhere. A great place for those who appreciate quality ingredients and a more refined K-BBQ experience.

Ordered meats and banchan from TBD and had a blast of a party at my place. The banchan was delicious and so easy to assemble, and the meat was conveniently packed, making total prep time for our party to be just 10 minutes! The meat was fresh, juicy and simply delicious. Our best find was the soy and gochujang marinated pork neck, though the pork belly and beef short rib were both amazing as well. Our only feedback, is if the beef short rib could be sliced very slightly shorter for ease of eating - the ones we had were as thick, and juicy as the size of an adult tongue.
Chanced upon this place and had lunch as I wanted to eat alot of meat. Abit disappointed as meat is over cooked looking burnt. But I enjoyed the $3 beer recommended by the staff.

visited the restaurant for dinner. was able to get a seat at the outdoor dining area w/o reservation.

ordered katsu, yukhoe, and perilla oil noodles (not pictured) and i have to say that they were all disappointing. while the katsu was quite sizable, the meat was tough. the sauce provided with the yukhoe was too sweet and salty and it made the dish really gelat, esp cos there wasn’t a lot of pear to help cut through the savoury taste. while i admit there is some level of human error involved (ie. definitely poured way too much of the sauce/gravy) i felt that the dish itself as a whole was slightly disappointing. the perilla oil noodles were the best out of what we ordered. the perilla oil flavour was quite mild compared to how it would taste like in korea, but that also means it would be more suitable for the singaporean taste buds. overall i believe that it could just be a poor choice of dishes ordered and am planning a return visit to try the other dishes.

didn’t purchase anything from the grocery section but saw lots of fresh cuts and prepared dinner packs.

Had a lovely dinner last nite at the restaurant - noodle with tartare .. and picked up my order of meal kits for dinner tonite … galbi jjim, chadol baegi tofujjigae, Mille-feuille nabe and chestnut bossam .. super easy to cook and super delicious .. like by family.. Thank you TBD !,

Thoroughly enjoyed the experience at this cozy boutique korean grocer-dining mart, the food here are fresh, and we selected the type of meat we wanted before getting them cooked in-house by the chefs. They included lots of freebies like the pink makgeoli shots, sides, and grilled veggies. We got the few types of meats, and all the pork and beef taste incredible. They even label the cut after grilling them! Beef ribs/outside skirt & Pork collar were my favourite, eaten together with the perilla leaves and (requested) raw garlic. The peeled tomatoes were so good we bought 2 jars of it home afterwards lol.

Overall, the space is meticulously designed and food/drink options are consciously chosen to provide a warm experience. The ambience is peaceful. Servers are attentive. And we also befriended one of the directors Lucy during our visit, it’s a very comfortably homely vibe to dine in. Highly recommended! Perhaps can consider coming around 6-6.30pm afterwork as families starting streaming in around 7-7.30pm

PS: the sorbet is too sweet for our liking
My go to Korean BBQ place. Just good quality stuff

I agree! this is real Korean food, made by real Koreans, with a (good) small twist… making it even more delicious and interesting . Decoration is simple… the magic is on the plate (or in the bowl) !! Hush!… one of these places that one likes to keep secret for oneself! 😉

Second time here and was appalled with the service I received at their butchery store.

I had a pleasant experience shopping during my first visit. Staffs were very attentive and welcoming, recommending and explaining the types of cuts + cooking methods for our knowledge. The products were decent but priced on the steeper side (but it's alright because the service were still decent).

But the second time I went, (I believed was a senior staff, Korean lady) was very inpatient. I first asked for an item that wasn't displayed on the shelves and she said no. Then I proceeded to browse the meats next, within the next min she asked if I needed any help, and I told her I'll take a look first and she showed me a black face..

Subsequently when we went done browsing and wanted to order, she ignored my signal (didn't even acknowledge me when I called her out several times) and went to serve another customer. While waiting for her to serve the other customer, she passed by showing us black face all the way, but was smiling from ear to ear with the other paying customer.

It was very disappointing experience.

📍THE BUTCHERS DINING
HIDDEN KOREAN FUSION GEM ??? why is this place not tiktok famous yet 😩😩 been here forever but still feels like a secret find 👀✨

Yeolmu Naengmyeon ($13) ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️/5
MY FAVORITE ALWAYS HAHAH 🌶️🧊 broth was RLLY punchy w sour kimchi + savoriness💋 tastes more like kimchi soup than usual sweet beef broth 🍜 noodles were SO firm & chewy like al dente pasta?! 🍝 not ur usual springy strands but super satisfying to bite 🤌🤌 crazy value for naengmyeon in SG 🤑💯

Kimchi Stew ($9) ⭐️⭐️/5
hmm not it tbh 😕 soup tasted kinda like FRENCH FRIES 🍟?? not bad just… weird LOL 😅 broth lacked depth 🫠 came super hot on a burner 🔥 lots of spam + pork belly inside 🐖 kimchi was vvv SOUR like aggressively so 🌀 not bad but also not memorable 🥲

LA Galbi Set ($24) ⭐️⭐️⭐️/5
bbq marinade WAS SO GOODDD 🔥🔥 rich, sweet-savory and stronger than most places 💯 beef not gamey or fatty at all which was 💕 but SUPER CHEWY 😵‍💫 jaw workout fr 😮‍💨 came w wraps, sauces, onions—solid full set 🌯🌶️ not cheap but fair enough for portion 👍

Hamburg Steak ($25) ❓/5
DIDN’T EVEN GET A BITE 😭 sis wiped the whole plate clean 💀💀 must be good right? 👀 said Tsukimi Hamburg’s was more flavourful tho 🌚 meat was a bit tough but sauce pour was fun to watch hehe 🍽️🎥

✨Ambience & Vibes✨
V cute & cozy!! felt like a hidden cafe 💖💕 NO QUEUE on a weekend bless 🙏✨ staff were SO NICE kept refilling our water without us asking 🥺💧and it’s FREEEE 🆓 ++ theres a Korean mart that sells MEAL KITS + RARE GROCERIES like imported vinegars, pickles, wines etc 🍷🧂 and you can get them to grill your meat RIGHT THERE 🐮🔥

💭 OVERALL:
SOSOSO shocked this place isn’t all over socials already?? 😭 prices decent and ambience is SO NICEEE 🫠💤  def gg back to try more dishes & maybe steal a bite of hamburg next time LOL 🐄🍽️

Food is very good and filling! Just pick the meat that you want and the chef will get it ready with all the side dishes/veges and all taste superb. They'll also serve kimchi beef soup!
Lady boss who is Korean was not very friendly and welcoming at all. Queried about the price of a packet of frozen meat that has no pricing label. She gave me a black face with an impatient response.
안창살과 토시살이 매우 훌륭해요. 우리는 일주일에 한번씩 주문하며 아이가 부드러운 토시살을 매우좋아합니다. 그리고 사장님께 원하는 부위를 말씀드리면 친철하게 응대해주시고 퀄리티 또한 좋습니다! 한국제품은 레드마트보다 저렴해요!

$25 per pax + $ for meat at your own selection at the display area. I love how the sides and grilled veggies are refillable, and the meat is cooked to the right doneness.

They cook the meat for you in the kitchen so you dont leave the place smelling like BBQ as well. This is my current go-to bbq place! But make sure to book in advance.

First time here — unfortunately, nothing to shout about.
The items are quite pricey, especially the steaks, which were surprisingly thin. Hard to justify paying almost $50 for a steak set that comes with just onion rings.

What made the experience worse was their reservation policy: they charge $90 upfront as a holding fee, even on a regular weekday like Wednesday. The frustrating part is that they didn’t mention this at all when we settled our bill. We only realized the next day and had to call them ourselves to ask about it — that’s when we were told it takes 4–5 business days for the refund.

With underwhelming food quality and a lack of transparency on their policies, there really isn’t much reason to come back for a second visit.

Made my first ever delivery order with The Butcher’s Dining (TBD) for a variety of their frozen fruits. Only after placing the order did I stumble upon some of the less-than-reassuring reviews about delayed deliveries and defrosted products.

Thankfully, none of that happened. The delivery arrived on the earlier end of the scheduled time slot, with everything properly packed in sealed foil bags and cushioned with ice packs. All items were still rock-solid frozen upon inspection.

Very pleased with this first experience—and definitely looking forward to ordering again soon. 👍🏼
Affordable and authentic, the go-to fix for no frills Korean bbq meat that’s not buffet or grilled at the table service.

Butchers store + Korean style bbq rolled in 1. Very unique compared to the usual Korean bbq joints. Nice to have it bbq in the kitchen so there's none of the heavy bbq smoke but all of the goodness of Korean grilled meats. The beef flanks were really tender and good, but the pork collar were rather dry and tough. The kimchi stew was very tasty along with the sides. They also serve Korean food you'd find in Korean restaurant and the kimchi pancakes were quite good too. A $25 service fee per pax for the grilled meats were a bit steep though.

어이가 없어서 태어나서 처음으로 구글리뷰 남깁니다. 웹사이트에 배달이 다음날 저녁 6시까지 된다고 나와있어서 배달시켰습니다.

1. 다음날 저녁으로 먹으려고 시켰는데 밤 9시반에 받았습니다.

2. Frozen이라고 써있는 백에 있던 LA갈비, 차돌박이 등등 다 녹아있었습니다.

3. Chilled라고 써있는 백에 있던 야채, 삼겹살은 얼마나 밖에 오래있었는지 뜨거웠습니다. 저희집 상온보다 뜨거운 야채와 고기를 받고 어이가 없었네요.

4. 리턴하고 환불받겠다고 전화했는데 내일 연락준다고 합니다.

이렇게 장사하는거 손님에게 민폐입니다. 누군 시간이 남아돌아서 금요일 밤에 이거 받을때까지 집에서 기다리고 앉아있어야 되나요?

I’m so shocked that I’m leaving a Google review for the first time in my life. I placed an order because the website stated that delivery would arrive by 6 PM the next day.

1.	I ordered it to have for dinner the next day, but I ended up receiving it at 9:30 PM.

2.	The LA galbi, brisket, and other items in the bag labeled “Frozen” were completely thawed.

3.	The vegetables and pork belly in the bag labeled “Chilled” were so warm that they were hotter than the room temperature in my house. I was speechless when I received vegetables and meat that were practically heated.

4.	I called to request a return and refund, and they told me they would contact me tomorrow.

I can’t believe a business is run this way in 2025. Just ridiculous.
Atas bbq. Great, high quality ingredients. Just abit short of staff
It's a nice and chill upscale Korean butchery with a minimalist concept.  The cafe was bright and airy, and the pork belly which I ordered was pretty fresh and decent.  The veggies were a nice bonus.
Good food, good service

Food quality was excellent!!
Everything we ordered tasted sooooo good!
The soup was rich and flavorful but find it too pricey. If only they can use have less meat option since we already ordered a meat dish. They do not serve banchan as well.
Overall the restaurant atmosphere was clean and felt comfortable dining there.

24 Nov 2024:
Found a gem of a restaurant! Was about to eat at Yahua BKT next door but the store front was too intriguing not to step in and take a look. They were a full house at that moment but managed to slot us in for an hour. I ordered the perilla oil noodles with yukhoe (raw beef) and my partner ordered the kalbi set. Both of us thoroughly enjoyed our meals. The perilla oil noodles was especially refreshing, especially because I had been driving all day running errands. We ordered some rice cakes for dessert but unfortunately they were quite subpar for us. Would definitely want to come back to try out their BBQs as the boss told us she hopes next time we can try their specialty meats :)

24 Jan 2025:
came back to try more dishes and was delighted to be treated to such a great meal. The pork chop quality was crazy, very good. The assorted pancakes were fresh and tasty. The pork collar set was of great quality as well. I liked the hand pulled Korean kimchi noodles as it was very refreshing.
Good service and delicious food.
Best meat quality in all of Singapore for Korean BBQ!
Really loved the concept of choosing your own meat and having them cook it. The sparkling makgeolli went very well with our grilled meat. Will be back again soon
Unique Korean BBQ experience at a butcher stall!! Meat was grilled perfectly! Juicy and flavourful!
Good food and the service staff were accommodating

My 2nd time at this place, this time with family. Meat was good, nice ambience. You select your own meat from the butchery and kitchen will grill it for you: Do note that they  charge $25/adult and $12/kid to grill the meat for ya. We ended up paying $90 just for them to grill the $60 meat we selected. Price is too steep IMO.

The customer service and attitude at this store is very much below standards. I experienced this now multiple times, where I walked out feeling mistreated by the rude store manager.
They mixed up my online order, never apologized, then when I picked up the order, missed an item forcing me to walk back to the store, but again without a proper apology, she just stuck the missing item into my shopping bag. The store items may be of good quality, but they are way over priced and you would expect better service at this price range.

Very quick service after u scan and send it your order.Water served with meal.Ample vegetables given for meat wrap and kimchi was just nice for me.Eat rice while it is hot as it tends to harden a bit when it has cooled down.
Thumbs up to price and quantity and location and service.Back 4th time already.
The shop has takeaway prepacked meal kits for the busy chef to prepare meals at home and perilla and sesame oil gift sets make good gifts.
U can also  choose and buy your favourite cuts of meat and have it grilled/cooked and served at the restaurant for a fee.

We've tried different Korean restaurants in Singapore and in Seoul, and this was really good! Amazing service, delicious meats and other dishes (mentaiko omelet), and nice selection of drinks. Love the store next to it as well for meal kits, pickled veg, corn tea, etc.

Food quality is excellent and value for money.

We had the short ribs, cajun chicken breast and pork collar. Chicken was soft and still moist despite the seasoning and grilling.

The kimchi stew was free flow and the set included a sorbet and Korean alcohol drink.

Good service and there was no smell as the bbq was done in an enclosed area.

Had their perilla oil noodles with yukhoe today and absolutely loved it! It was appetising and well presented, and most critically the meat was fresh. Will definitely be back for this - I hope it continues to stay on the menu.
Great value for money, food quality is excellent. Service is solid though sometimes shorthanded (who isn't?). Great spot for lunch.

Me and my hubby love this place ! We found this hidden gam after getting markegolli here . There’s a Korean lady who is always so attentive and warm ! Always nice seeing her ! Food is so so good! Always enjoy eating here !

The service staff is honestly good with their service. Had a complemantary snack. Was going nearby for a meeting and decided to go there for a drink while waiting.

All was good until I heard the gentleman inside say, 买一杯水而已， 坐到将久!

Dude, if you guys want to close for break or there's a time limit, could have just told me right? If want to 讲坏话, make sure your patron don't hear?

That being said, the drinks is good, service is good as well MINUS what I have heard....

Absolutely love this place. Huge selection of drinks, and really high quality meats. Their marinades are all fantastic and not overly heavy. Plus the burger and fries are top notch .

5/5. Big recommendation

We found this place while searching for a Korean butcher/grocer which sells galbijim. Turns out it has a restaurant with outdoor seats that dine in with our dog. Food is reasonably priced and delicious too.

Short review

Dessert
👍🏻the mix is good. A mix of hot cold. A mix of blend and sweet. Two item separated that is little lonely to eat coming together with matching perfection.

Staff
🫳🏻didnt interact with staff much so, who knows

Atmosphere
👍🏻nice ambience
👍🏻nice seating and decorating
Amazing butcher and Korean grocery shop!

My 2nd time here for the beef tartare,  the dish is fresh, tasty and value for money.  The sparking Boksoondoga (red rice favour) is great taste, when I visited there is a 15% discount. In addition, this restaurant sells the cheapest  obksoondoga  makkgeoli.

I also love the grocery area which one can buy the fresh cut and get the chef to cook and serve, with a charge of S$25 (excluding the meats' costs).

Pancakes (aka jeon) taste great too, so does the corn dogs.

Since it is Singapore's 59 National Day, there is free kueh pie ti being served on the house, and I love it since there is squid in the stuffing.

First time tried out this place with my girl friends over the weekend & I simply loce how you can pick the freshly packed meats & have it grilled by the kitchen staffs. Love the wide variety of beverages available and the presentation of the food.

Lastly I would like to give my complements to the manager, Lucy.  Something unpleasant happened during our meal, she acted calmly, quickly and making sure we were all satisfied with her resolutions. Appreciate her excellent cuetomer service provided & we will definitely recommend this place to our friends. Thank you 🫶🏻

Amazing beef and food! We came here on a weekend and ordered the k-bbq (only available on weekends) and the meat was marinated very well, cooked and served on a pan, and the cuts of beef are the best if you’re a person that hates fats in the beef. The pork was also done well, just quite fatty, but honestly speaking from a meat fat hater, I still loved the pork!

The rice was good quality and top-notch; also came with a bowl of kimchi soup, tofu and meat included. Very happy experience and if you’re not driving, you can also order the makgeoli. Meal kits are also provided with step-by-step instructions on the TV outside.

The place was pretty small, but packed. Thank god we placed a reservation. The toilets and facilities are spotless. The sink outside requires you to push down on a foot pedal for it to work. The first time I did it, I got confused. I highly recommend the pork cutlet and the k-bbq.

I've always bought my makgeolli from The Butcher’s Dining, but I never had a chance to try their restaurant until yesterday. My friend and I decided to dine in, and we both enjoyed the experience immensely.

We ordered the BBQ pork collar, kimchi with spam soup, and assorted pancakes. The pork collar was nicely marinated and well BBQ'd, still juicy and tender. The pancakes had a slight crisp on the outside but were chewy inside. The food was of high quality and absolutely delicious. The service was also excellent, making our dining experience even more enjoyable.

The sparkling makgeolli, my favorite, was reasonably priced—half of what other Korean BBQ restaurants charge. It’s a steal here!

Overall, a fantastic dining experience. I will definitely come again. Highly recommended!
담은 막걸리 맛있음

とても美味しかったです。
ランチでの利用でした、お肉の追加、ユッケをセットに追加しました。
良い意味でボリュームがあり、パンパンでした。
味付けもさっぱりしてて、また利用したいです。
집근처여서 자주 가는 곳 입니다. 잡내 안나는 고기사서 먹기도 좋고 밥하기 귀찮은 날 밀키트 사서 잘 맛있게 먹는 곳이에요~~ 직원 분들도 친절하시고 좋습니다

Went a few times and it was great. Love the concept where you select the meats and you have them cooked. Went back today and we were asked to pay $25 per head to grill the meats. Our 4 year old daughter had to pay $12.50 as well! The meats are pricey to begin with, and with this new arrangement there is no longer any value in patronising this place. I guess the owner got too greedy. Now we understand why the place was so empty for a Saturday lunch hour.

If you want bbq meats you have to pay $25 per pax on top of the cost of the meats which you purchase at the shop. It’s kinda steep. Not that it’s not yummy. But I just feel the $25 per pax price tag makes the meal over the top. The sides are nice and they do serve you sides that are slightly different from the usual Korean bbq. But it won’t be a weekly thing for me.

Love the concept of the diner.

The butcher - the meats are great!  Great value for good meats.

Meal service - they cook their meats very well and the side dishes are refreshing and light, helps to cut the oil from the meat.

Prepackaged food - Great options if you are looking to have korean at home. Easy and convenient

Service - The staff there are knowledgable and provide great service especially when you are dining there.

Parking - free but limited parking in front of the location
In addition to a wide selection of beef and pork, they also have a great selection of sous vide chicken. Highly recommend the Cajun chicken, Basil Chicken and the newly launched Smoked Duck!

우연히 숙소 앞에 있는 매장을 보고 들어갔는데 한국식 정육점과 고기집을 같이 운영하고 계시더라구요! 저희는 한국음식을 볼 수 없는 불모지에서 외노자로 일하는 중이라 눈이 뒤집혀 바로 LA갈비와 항정살,오겹살 사왔습니다. 정육점에 계신 사장님(?) 매니저(?) 여자분께서 LA갈비가 유명하다하셨는데 집에 와서 구워먹어보니 진짜 유명할 만한 맛이었습니다🥹 양도 많고 퀄리티 대비 가격도 좋았어요. 같은 시간 구매하러 오신 중년 여자손님께서 양념 돼지목살도 진짜 맛있다고 추천해주셨지만 짐이 많아 사지 못한게 너무 아쉽습니다.. 껍데기가 붙어있는 오겹살로는 냉제육을 해서 먹었는데 고기와 지방의 비율도 적절하고 냄새나지도 않아서 너무 맛있게 잘먹었어요. 거기서 판매하고 있는 고추장아찌도 매콤하니 맛있었어요. (항정살은 아직 먹기 전이라 후기가 없습니다) 그리고 응대해주신 여자분께서 너무 친절하셔서 기분이 좋았습니다! 싱가포르에 또 가게되면 무조건 들러서 또 사올거에요!!
food & beef is amazing! must try!

Paying $24 for 2 pax for "grilling fee" was initially understandable as I thought they had to "earn" their revenue somewhere. But the side dishes provided were barely any good (cost price of those probably don't even amount to $3-4). The meat cuts are decent but at the price point it is only average (they also don't allow customers to specify the amount of weight - you just gotta select from one of their pre-packaged products). While all the above can be forgivable, the worst part of the experience was that the lady boss (presumably korean) only treats and is attentive to Korean customers. Very poor and unprofessional in that sense. Reason why it still deserved 1 star was that at least there's some potential (as long as service is improved and the owner adopts a better attitude)
Dog-friendly outdoor seating. Lots of mosquitoes so ask the staff for insect repellant. Otherwise, food is great!

A nice Korean bbq place, you choose the meat, they’ll bbq it for you.. Their side dishes was amazing.
Excellent service (they offered ginger honey to my little girl, who they notice was coughing)
Great place to get your red rice makgeolli fix. Also meats.

Owner refused to allow dine in on Sat afternoon  if we do not order grilled bbq meat even when the restaurant is half full, and the fact we ordered more expensive food than what they can earn simply because they insisted on their company policy. Highly inflexible restaurant, even a fine dining restaurant can be more flexible than this. This is a typical Singapore establishment which is always less flexible than when I traveled overseas.  Will not recommend at all.

Lovely Korean BBQ Resturant !!!

Good quality meat cuts and the place is clean and bright.

Not smoky

This place is amazing! Wide variety of korean products, its like a mini grocery. They have have their own dining space, nice ambiance, spacious, and quiet. And to tell you, they have their own butcher for korean quality meat and friendly staffs. Ill be back here to fulfill my cravings for it and bring more friends over. ⭐️
整體而言，乾乾淨淨的店面，很舒服的現代感餐廳。很有韓式現代風情。週末的烤肉活動很不錯，自己挑選肉讓主廚烤。比較與韓國餐廳不一樣的是蔬菜、泡菜都是加點要收費，兩個人吃一餐下來消費大概在250新幣左右～

Nice ambience. They offer bbq fri night until Sunday where you can select your choice of meat. We picked pork jowl and tried beef flap tail first time total price at 47dollars. Booked for 2 pax grilling service charge which comes with banchan and side veggies for 12 dollars per person minimum 2 pax. Got sparkling water for the hubby who’s allergic to alcohol and jinyeong makgeolli for myself. Would recommend to book ahead, we walked in and the Korean lady was nice enough to accomodate us but with a 75min table time. nice touch for free makgeolli shot.

Lucy It’s doesn’t make sense to push a customer slot 1 hour later just because you accommodated another group of customer in after they came very late. You told me yr policy is no later than 15mins. And only call to inform us 20mins before our time slot. Why are we penalized? Meat is awesome but customers service is not awesome!

I discovered this store through an advertisement on IG and decided to visit today. I purchased coffee beans and two packs of beef. Prices are on the higher side, but compared to so many other kbbq places, I feel it's better value for the money! You don't smell of cooking when you leave because it's all done for you and also, if you're lazy or have a hyperactive kid like me, see above. TBD are open for dinner too so please check their website for opening times. The menu is ever evolving so there’s always something new to discover. Go try it and thank me later.
Quality of meat, service and ambience is great! Highly recommended
It’s my hidden gem! Every single dish is always good and the staff is just so friendly. I particularly love their pork cutlet and the somen dish

Manager is very enthusiastic and accommodating. My family has frequented this restaurant since its opening and can be relied on for their consistency. We truly enjoy the warmth and service here! :)

This have been a regular dinning spot for me and family. It have a very friendly atmosphere and staff. Menu will differ from time to time. Always a new experience. The beef looks superb. There are many artisanal sauces and pastes to choose from. Good for gifting.

I brought a Rib and out skirt. The meat here is really good! Most importantly, it does not smell like meat. It is even cheaper than other stores, such as Korean restaurants and restaurants.
I don't know why the review here isn't good!!
I'll go here whenever I want to eat meat dishes and Korean BBQ!!  Above all, the female worker who seemed to be the owner of this store was very kind to us.
I love this place! Good service, consistently good quality variety of meat & their meal kits are top with no MSG. Nice variety of authentic korean products too!
One of the best Korean meat places I’ve ever been to. Brilliant food, impeccable service. 10/10 would recommend going for the weekend grilled meats.

The restaurant have two modes: pick their menu or pick their fresh meat and they will grill for you. Only their pre sliced meats are allowed for grilling. You will have to make payment first before moving in to the restaurant. No complaints on table service. Because the meat is fresh, it won't be fully marinated when served to you in such a short time. Vegetables here is not free flow like typical Korean restaurants. I made a few complaints on the serving size of kimchi and marinated white carrot because I find it ridiculous that I have to share 3 pieces of white carrot between my companion and myself...
The customer service really need to be improved. Especially the Korean lady at the counter, her tone was so rude. It is not worth going back to support.

Contrary to many of the negative reviews here. I actually believe this place deserves more praise. Will definitely come back again!

A new kbbq dining experience whereby the cooking is all done by the staff in the kitchen while we just sit and wait to be served.

Quaint and cosy korean cafe-restaurant with delicious authentic Korean set lunches and very affordable Korean craft beer. Support the Korean lady butcher who has been recently featured on CNA. Recommend the galbi beef set, kimchi pork set and steak tartare bimbimbap.
Very nice and delicious Korean food. Servings are big and worth the price charged.

We’ve been coming regularly and always happy with friendly staff and great food.

Amazing food with good draft beer! Will definitely be back for more
Always a great meal made with quality produce here.  Perilla oil noodles is a must try,

Discovered this spot through a friend, and it really stands out from the usual K-BBQ joints along Tanjong Pagar. The key difference? The quality of the meat. There’s a dedicated counter where you can choose your preferred cuts, and the team grills them to your ideal doneness. They do serve a small selection of noodles, stews, etc.

You can also buy the raw cuts to take home and cook on your own. Bonus points for their curated selection of makgeolli, featuring unique labels you don’t typically see elsewhere. A great place for those who appreciate quality ingredients and a more refined K-BBQ experience.

Ordered meats and banchan from TBD and had a blast of a party at my place. The banchan was delicious and so easy to assemble, and the meat was conveniently packed, making total prep time for our party to be just 10 minutes! The meat was fresh, juicy and simply delicious. Our best find was the soy and gochujang marinated pork neck, though the pork belly and beef short rib were both amazing as well. Our only feedback, is if the beef short rib could be sliced very slightly shorter for ease of eating - the ones we had were as thick, and juicy as the size of an adult tongue.
Chanced upon this place and had lunch as I wanted to eat alot of meat. Abit disappointed as meat is over cooked looking burnt. But I enjoyed the $3 beer recommended by the staff.

visited the restaurant for dinner. was able to get a seat at the outdoor dining area w/o reservation.

ordered katsu, yukhoe, and perilla oil noodles (not pictured) and i have to say that they were all disappointing. while the katsu was quite sizable, the meat was tough. the sauce provided with the yukhoe was too sweet and salty and it made the dish really gelat, esp cos there wasn’t a lot of pear to help cut through the savoury taste. while i admit there is some level of human error involved (ie. definitely poured way too much of the sauce/gravy) i felt that the dish itself as a whole was slightly disappointing. the perilla oil noodles were the best out of what we ordered. the perilla oil flavour was quite mild compared to how it would taste like in korea, but that also means it would be more suitable for the singaporean taste buds. overall i believe that it could just be a poor choice of dishes ordered and am planning a return visit to try the other dishes.

didn’t purchase anything from the grocery section but saw lots of fresh cuts and prepared dinner packs.

Had a lovely dinner last nite at the restaurant - noodle with tartare .. and picked up my order of meal kits for dinner tonite … galbi jjim, chadol baegi tofujjigae, Mille-feuille nabe and chestnut bossam .. super easy to cook and super delicious .. like by family.. Thank you TBD !,

Thoroughly enjoyed the experience at this cozy boutique korean grocer-dining mart, the food here are fresh, and we selected the type of meat we wanted before getting them cooked in-house by the chefs. They included lots of freebies like the pink makgeoli shots, sides, and grilled veggies. We got the few types of meats, and all the pork and beef taste incredible. They even label the cut after grilling them! Beef ribs/outside skirt & Pork collar were my favourite, eaten together with the perilla leaves and (requested) raw garlic. The peeled tomatoes were so good we bought 2 jars of it home afterwards lol.

Overall, the space is meticulously designed and food/drink options are consciously chosen to provide a warm experience. The ambience is peaceful. Servers are attentive. And we also befriended one of the directors Lucy during our visit, it’s a very comfortably homely vibe to dine in. Highly recommended! Perhaps can consider coming around 6-6.30pm afterwork as families starting streaming in around 7-7.30pm

PS: the sorbet is too sweet for our liking
My go to Korean BBQ place. Just good quality stuff

I agree! this is real Korean food, made by real Koreans, with a (good) small twist… making it even more delicious and interesting . Decoration is simple… the magic is on the plate (or in the bowl) !! Hush!… one of these places that one likes to keep secret for oneself! 😉

Second time here and was appalled with the service I received at their butchery store.

I had a pleasant experience shopping during my first visit. Staffs were very attentive and welcoming, recommending and explaining the types of cuts + cooking methods for our knowledge. The products were decent but priced on the steeper side (but it's alright because the service were still decent).

But the second time I went, (I believed was a senior staff, Korean lady) was very inpatient. I first asked for an item that wasn't displayed on the shelves and she said no. Then I proceeded to browse the meats next, within the next min she asked if I needed any help, and I told her I'll take a look first and she showed me a black face..

Subsequently when we went done browsing and wanted to order, she ignored my signal (didn't even acknowledge me when I called her out several times) and went to serve another customer. While waiting for her to serve the other customer, she passed by showing us black face all the way, but was smiling from ear to ear with the other paying customer.

It was very disappointing experience.

Lady boss who is Korean was not very friendly and welcoming at all. Queried about the price of a packet of frozen meat that has no pricing label. She gave me a black face with an impatient response.
안창살과 토시살이 매우 훌륭해요. 우리는 일주일에 한번씩 주문하며 아이가 부드러운 토시살을 매우좋아합니다. 그리고 사장님께 원하는 부위를 말씀드리면 친철하게 응대해주시고 퀄리티 또한 좋습니다! 한국제품은 레드마트보다 저렴해요!

$25 per pax + $ for meat at your own selection at the display area. I love how the sides and grilled veggies are refillable, and the meat is cooked to the right doneness.

They cook the meat for you in the kitchen so you dont leave the place smelling like BBQ as well. This is my current go-to bbq place! But make sure to book in advance.

First time here — unfortunately, nothing to shout about.
The items are quite pricey, especially the steaks, which were surprisingly thin. Hard to justify paying almost $50 for a steak set that comes with just onion rings.

What made the experience worse was their reservation policy: they charge $90 upfront as a holding fee, even on a regular weekday like Wednesday. The frustrating part is that they didn’t mention this at all when we settled our bill. We only realized the next day and had to call them ourselves to ask about it — that’s when we were told it takes 4–5 business days for the refund.

With underwhelming food quality and a lack of transparency on their policies, there really isn’t much reason to come back for a second visit.

Made my first ever delivery order with The Butcher’s Dining (TBD) for a variety of their frozen fruits. Only after placing the order did I stumble upon some of the less-than-reassuring reviews about delayed deliveries and defrosted products.

Thankfully, none of that happened. The delivery arrived on the earlier end of the scheduled time slot, with everything properly packed in sealed foil bags and cushioned with ice packs. All items were still rock-solid frozen upon inspection.

Very pleased with this first experience—and definitely looking forward to ordering again soon. 👍🏼
Affordable and authentic, the go-to fix for no frills Korean bbq meat that’s not buffet or grilled at the table service.

Butchers store + Korean style bbq rolled in 1. Very unique compared to the usual Korean bbq joints. Nice to have it bbq in the kitchen so there's none of the heavy bbq smoke but all of the goodness of Korean grilled meats. The beef flanks were really tender and good, but the pork collar were rather dry and tough. The kimchi stew was very tasty along with the sides. They also serve Korean food you'd find in Korean restaurant and the kimchi pancakes were quite good too. A $25 service fee per pax for the grilled meats were a bit steep though.

4. 리턴하고 환불받겠다고 전화했는데 내일 연락준다고 합니다.

I’m so shocked that I’m leaving a Google review for the first time in my life. I placed an order because the website stated that delivery would arrive by 6 PM the next day.

1.	I ordered it to have for dinner the next day, but I ended up receiving it at 9:30 PM.

2.	The LA galbi, brisket, and other items in the bag labeled “Frozen” were completely thawed.

3.	The vegetables and pork belly in the bag labeled “Chilled” were so warm that they were hotter than the room temperature in my house. I was speechless when I received vegetables and meat that were practically heated.

4.	I called to request a return and refund, and they told me they would contact me tomorrow.

I can’t believe a business is run this way in 2025. Just ridiculous.
Atas bbq. Great, high quality ingredients. Just abit short of staff
It's a nice and chill upscale Korean butchery with a minimalist concept.  The cafe was bright and airy, and the pork belly which I ordered was pretty fresh and decent.  The veggies were a nice bonus.
Good food, good service

Food quality was excellent!!
Everything we ordered tasted sooooo good!
The soup was rich and flavorful but find it too pricey. If only they can use have less meat option since we already ordered a meat dish. They do not serve banchan as well.
Overall the restaurant atmosphere was clean and felt comfortable dining there.

24 Nov 2024:
Found a gem of a restaurant! Was about to eat at Yahua BKT next door but the store front was too intriguing not to step in and take a look. They were a full house at that moment but managed to slot us in for an hour. I ordered the perilla oil noodles with yukhoe (raw beef) and my partner ordered the kalbi set. Both of us thoroughly enjoyed our meals. The perilla oil noodles was especially refreshing, especially because I had been driving all day running errands. We ordered some rice cakes for dessert but unfortunately they were quite subpar for us. Would definitely want to come back to try out their BBQs as the boss told us she hopes next time we can try their specialty meats :)

24 Jan 2025:
came back to try more dishes and was delighted to be treated to such a great meal. The pork chop quality was crazy, very good. The assorted pancakes were fresh and tasty. The pork collar set was of great quality as well. I liked the hand pulled Korean kimchi noodles as it was very refreshing.
Good service and delicious food.
Best meat quality in all of Singapore for Korean BBQ!
Really loved the concept of choosing your own meat and having them cook it. The sparkling makgeolli went very well with our grilled meat. Will be back again soon
Unique Korean BBQ experience at a butcher stall!! Meat was grilled perfectly! Juicy and flavourful!
Good food and the service staff were accommodating

My 2nd time at this place, this time with family. Meat was good, nice ambience. You select your own meat from the butchery and kitchen will grill it for you: Do note that they  charge $25/adult and $12/kid to grill the meat for ya. We ended up paying $90 just for them to grill the $60 meat we selected. Price is too steep IMO.

The customer service and attitude at this store is very much below standards. I experienced this now multiple times, where I walked out feeling mistreated by the rude store manager.
They mixed up my online order, never apologized, then when I picked up the order, missed an item forcing me to walk back to the store, but again without a proper apology, she just stuck the missing item into my shopping bag. The store items may be of good quality, but they are way over priced and you would expect better service at this price range.

Very quick service after u scan and send it your order.Water served with meal.Ample vegetables given for meat wrap and kimchi was just nice for me.Eat rice while it is hot as it tends to harden a bit when it has cooled down.
Thumbs up to price and quantity and location and service.Back 4th time already.
The shop has takeaway prepacked meal kits for the busy chef to prepare meals at home and perilla and sesame oil gift sets make good gifts.
U can also  choose and buy your favourite cuts of meat and have it grilled/cooked and served at the restaurant for a fee.

We've tried different Korean restaurants in Singapore and in Seoul, and this was really good! Amazing service, delicious meats and other dishes (mentaiko omelet), and nice selection of drinks. Love the store next to it as well for meal kits, pickled veg, corn tea, etc.

Food quality is excellent and value for money.

We had the short ribs, cajun chicken breast and pork collar. Chicken was soft and still moist despite the seasoning and grilling.

The kimchi stew was free flow and the set included a sorbet and Korean alcohol drink.

Good service and there was no smell as the bbq was done in an enclosed area.

Had their perilla oil noodles with yukhoe today and absolutely loved it! It was appetising and well presented, and most critically the meat was fresh. Will definitely be back for this - I hope it continues to stay on the menu.
Great value for money, food quality is excellent. Service is solid though sometimes shorthanded (who isn't?). Great spot for lunch.

Me and my hubby love this place ! We found this hidden gam after getting markegolli here . There’s a Korean lady who is always so attentive and warm ! Always nice seeing her ! Food is so so good! Always enjoy eating here !

The service staff is honestly good with their service. Had a complemantary snack. Was going nearby for a meeting and decided to go there for a drink while waiting.

All was good until I heard the gentleman inside say, 买一杯水而已， 坐到将久!

Dude, if you guys want to close for break or there's a time limit, could have just told me right? If want to 讲坏话, make sure your patron don't hear?

That being said, the drinks is good, service is good as well MINUS what I have heard....

Absolutely love this place. Huge selection of drinks, and really high quality meats. Their marinades are all fantastic and not overly heavy. Plus the burger and fries are top notch .

5/5. Big recommendation

We found this place while searching for a Korean butcher/grocer which sells galbijim. Turns out it has a restaurant with outdoor seats that dine in with our dog. Food is reasonably priced and delicious too.

Short review
I was nearby and wanted desserts.

Dessert
👍🏻the mix is good. A mix of hot cold. A mix of blend and sweet. Two item separated that is little lonely to eat coming together with matching perfection.

Staff
🫳🏻didnt interact with staff much so, who knows

Atmosphere
👍🏻nice ambience
👍🏻nice seating and decorating
Amazing butcher and Korean grocery shop!

My 2nd time here for the beef tartare,  the dish is fresh, tasty and value for money.  The sparking Boksoondoga (red rice favour) is great taste, when I visited there is a 15% discount. In addition, this restaurant sells the cheapest  obksoondoga  makkgeoli.

I also love the grocery area which one can buy the fresh cut and get the chef to cook and serve, with a charge of S$25 (excluding the meats' costs).

Pancakes (aka jeon) taste great too, so does the corn dogs.

Since it is Singapore's 59 National Day, there is free kueh pie ti being served on the house, and I love it since there is squid in the stuffing.

First time tried out this place with my girl friends over the weekend & I simply loce how you can pick the freshly packed meats & have it grilled by the kitchen staffs. Love the wide variety of beverages available and the presentation of the food.

Lastly I would like to give my complements to the manager, Lucy.  Something unpleasant happened during our meal, she acted calmly, quickly and making sure we were all satisfied with her resolutions. Appreciate her excellent cuetomer service provided & we will definitely recommend this place to our friends. Thank you 🫶🏻

Amazing beef and food! We came here on a weekend and ordered the k-bbq (only available on weekends) and the meat was marinated very well, cooked and served on a pan, and the cuts of beef are the best if you’re a person that hates fats in the beef. The pork was also done well, just quite fatty, but honestly speaking from a meat fat hater, I still loved the pork!

The rice was good quality and top-notch; also came with a bowl of kimchi soup, tofu and meat included. Very happy experience and if you’re not driving, you can also order the makgeoli. Meal kits are also provided with step-by-step instructions on the TV outside.

The place was pretty small, but packed. Thank god we placed a reservation. The toilets and facilities are spotless. The sink outside requires you to push down on a foot pedal for it to work. The first time I did it, I got confused. I highly recommend the pork cutlet and the k-bbq.

I've always bought my makgeolli from The Butcher’s Dining, but I never had a chance to try their restaurant until yesterday. My friend and I decided to dine in, and we both enjoyed the experience immensely.

We ordered the BBQ pork collar, kimchi with spam soup, and assorted pancakes. The pork collar was nicely marinated and well BBQ'd, still juicy and tender. The pancakes had a slight crisp on the outside but were chewy inside. The food was of high quality and absolutely delicious. The service was also excellent, making our dining experience even more enjoyable.

The sparkling makgeolli, my favorite, was reasonably priced—half of what other Korean BBQ restaurants charge. It’s a steal here!

Overall, a fantastic dining experience. I will definitely come again. Highly recommended!
담은 막걸리 맛있음

とても美味しかったです。
ランチでの利用でした、お肉の追加、ユッケをセットに追加しました。
良い意味でボリュームがあり、パンパンでした。
味付けもさっぱりしてて、また利用したいです。
집근처여서 자주 가는 곳 입니다. 잡내 안나는 고기사서 먹기도 좋고 밥하기 귀찮은 날 밀키트 사서 잘 맛있게 먹는 곳이에요~~ 직원 분들도 친절하시고 좋습니다

Went a few times and it was great. Love the concept where you select the meats and you have them cooked. Went back today and we were asked to pay $25 per head to grill the meats. Our 4 year old daughter had to pay $12.50 as well! The meats are pricey to begin with, and with this new arrangement there is no longer any value in patronising this place. I guess the owner got too greedy. Now we understand why the place was so empty for a Saturday lunch hour.

If you want bbq meats you have to pay $25 per pax on top of the cost of the meats which you purchase at the shop. It’s kinda steep. Not that it’s not yummy. But I just feel the $25 per pax price tag makes the meal over the top. The sides are nice and they do serve you sides that are slightly different from the usual Korean bbq. But it won’t be a weekly thing for me.

Love the concept of the diner.

The butcher - the meats are great!  Great value for good meats.

Meal service - they cook their meats very well and the side dishes are refreshing and light, helps to cut the oil from the meat.

Prepackaged food - Great options if you are looking to have korean at home. Easy and convenient

Service - The staff there are knowledgable and provide great service especially when you are dining there.

Parking - free but limited parking in front of the location
In addition to a wide selection of beef and pork, they also have a great selection of sous vide chicken. Highly recommend the Cajun chicken, Basil Chicken and the newly launched Smoked Duck!

우연히 숙소 앞에 있는 매장을 보고 들어갔는데 한국식 정육점과 고기집을 같이 운영하고 계시더라구요! 저희는 한국음식을 볼 수 없는 불모지에서 외노자로 일하는 중이라 눈이 뒤집혀 바로 LA갈비와 항정살,오겹살 사왔습니다. 정육점에 계신 사장님(?) 매니저(?) 여자분께서 LA갈비가 유명하다하셨는데 집에 와서 구워먹어보니 진짜 유명할 만한 맛이었습니다🥹 양도 많고 퀄리티 대비 가격도 좋았어요. 같은 시간 구매하러 오신 중년 여자손님께서 양념 돼지목살도 진짜 맛있다고 추천해주셨지만 짐이 많아 사지 못한게 너무 아쉽습니다.. 껍데기가 붙어있는 오겹살로는 냉제육을 해서 먹었는데 고기와 지방의 비율도 적절하고 냄새나지도 않아서 너무 맛있게 잘먹었어요. 거기서 판매하고 있는 고추장아찌도 매콤하니 맛있었어요. (항정살은 아직 먹기 전이라 후기가 없습니다) 그리고 응대해주신 여자분께서 너무 친절하셔서 기분이 좋았습니다! 싱가포르에 또 가게되면 무조건 들러서 또 사올거에요!!
food & beef is amazing! must try!

Paying $24 for 2 pax for "grilling fee" was initially understandable as I thought they had to "earn" their revenue somewhere. But the side dishes provided were barely any good (cost price of those probably don't even amount to $3-4). The meat cuts are decent but at the price point it is only average (they also don't allow customers to specify the amount of weight - you just gotta select from one of their pre-packaged products). While all the above can be forgivable, the worst part of the experience was that the lady boss (presumably korean) only treats and is attentive to Korean customers. Very poor and unprofessional in that sense. Reason why it still deserved 1 star was that at least there's some potential (as long as service is improved and the owner adopts a better attitude)
Dog-friendly outdoor seating. Lots of mosquitoes so ask the staff for insect repellant. Otherwise, food is great!

A nice Korean bbq place, you choose the meat, they’ll bbq it for you.. Their side dishes was amazing.
Excellent service (they offered ginger honey to my little girl, who they notice was coughing)
Great place to get your red rice makgeolli fix. Also meats.

Owner refused to allow dine in on Sat afternoon  if we do not order grilled bbq meat even when the restaurant is half full, and the fact we ordered more expensive food than what they can earn simply because they insisted on their company policy. Highly inflexible restaurant, even a fine dining restaurant can be more flexible than this. This is a typical Singapore establishment which is always less flexible than when I traveled overseas.  Will not recommend at all.

Lovely Korean BBQ Resturant !!!

Good quality meat cuts and the place is clean and bright.

Not smoky

This place is amazing! Wide variety of korean products, its like a mini grocery. They have have their own dining space, nice ambiance, spacious, and quiet. And to tell you, they have their own butcher for korean quality meat and friendly staffs. Ill be back here to fulfill my cravings for it and bring more friends over. ⭐️
整體而言，乾乾淨淨的店面，很舒服的現代感餐廳。很有韓式現代風情。週末的烤肉活動很不錯，自己挑選肉讓主廚烤。比較與韓國餐廳不一樣的是蔬菜、泡菜都是加點要收費，兩個人吃一餐下來消費大概在250新幣左右～

Nice ambience. They offer bbq fri night until Sunday where you can select your choice of meat. We picked pork jowl and tried beef flap tail first time total price at 47dollars. Booked for 2 pax grilling service charge which comes with banchan and side veggies for 12 dollars per person minimum 2 pax. Got sparkling water for the hubby who’s allergic to alcohol and jinyeong makgeolli for myself. Would recommend to book ahead, we walked in and the Korean lady was nice enough to accomodate us but with a 75min table time. nice touch for free makgeolli shot.

Lucy It’s doesn’t make sense to push a customer slot 1 hour later just because you accommodated another group of customer in after they came very late. You told me yr policy is no later than 15mins. And only call to inform us 20mins before our time slot. Why are we penalized? Meat is awesome but customers service is not awesome!

I discovered this store through an advertisement on IG and decided to visit today. I purchased coffee beans and two packs of beef. Although the prices were a bit higher than expected, what disappointed me the most was the demeanor of the female staff members. Both the cashier and the staff member at the butchery counter gave me a unwarranted dirty look. It made me feel unwelcome and uncomfortable. Their lack of friendliness and absence of smiles mirrored some of the low-rating reviews I’ve seen here. Unfortunately, this experience has left me with no intention of returning to the store or recommending it to others

I finally get to try this place despite walking past many time. I am a little late to discover this gem. The lunch set is really tasty. We had the beef and pork belly set. This place definitely deserve more coverage and exposure. For those who wants to have korean food , do check out this place if ur in the tiong bahru vicinity

First visit after seeing reviews online The meat, esp LA galbi!! didn't disappoint, loved the yukhoe as well.
Thank u for the attentive service, for providing ginger tea for my sil who was coughing!
Will definitely recommend and will be back :)

Ordered Yuja Mint ice tea, Tail flap wagyu and Yukhoe (raw beef tartare). Fantastic experience and ambience. Generous portions, amazing service, came with complementary Mukgeoli shots and kimchi beef soup. Will 100% return

We love coming to The Butcher's Dining for family lunch on the weekends because of the weekend BBQ! The staff are always so welcoming and helpful, particularly the Lady Boss. You'll have to pay for your meat and then the BBQ accompaniments (veggies, banchan and grilling fee) before you can eat, but it's definitely worth it to me!

The meats they sell are really top quality (love love love the LA galbi) and my 3-year old can wolf down a whole portion of the rice by herself. Vegetables for the ssam wraps are always fresh and I love how they give each person a perilla leaf, which is such a unique flavour. The space is lovely and intimate too.

Prices are on the higher side, but compared to so many other kbbq places, I feel it's better value for the money! You don't smell of cooking when you leave because it's all done for you and also, if you're lazy or have a hyperactive kid like me, see above. No need to wait for the charcoal to be ready or to cut the meat yourself because it's all done already!

Kamsahamida, TBD!
Unique K BBQ concept with the ability to pick your own meat and then they cook it for you so no mess and the meat is delicious! Definitely be back!

it was my second time here and still feel super satisfied. ordered the same thing as last time cuz i really missed them. galbitang set (beef soup) not too oily,comes with the rich buttery aroma... i finished the rice tho i supposed to be on diet...
old school pork cutlet. big portion and very crunchy.... not too oily but still a bit sinful....lol

This has been my go to place for premium meats and Korean produce. The butchery and grocery is at the front of the store with an attached dining area. I have dined in many times and the food has never disappointed. The lunch sets especially the Doroc pork fillet, Jajang Rice and pork belly bossam wrap are outstanding and hit the mark when you just need a delicious lunch. TBD are open for dinner too so please check their website for opening times. The menu is ever evolving so there’s always something new to discover. Go try it and thank me later.
Quality of meat, service and ambience is great! Highly recommended
It’s my hidden gem! Every single dish is always good and the staff is just so friendly. I particularly love their pork cutlet and the somen dish

been a big fan of TBD since they started and have been coming here for their lunch & dinner. service is always good and i love the quality and uniqueness of their food! bbq grilled for you is the best in sg imo

Back for the 2nd time in the consecutive sunday! Great service and food recommendation by the ever friendly lady boss. The meat is cooked just nice and tasty!  The environment is nice and we love the playlist too! :)
Manager is very enthusiastic and accommodating. My family has frequented this restaurant since its opening and can be relied on for their consistency. We truly enjoy the warmth and service here! :)

This have been a regular dinning spot for me and family. It have a very friendly atmosphere and staff. Menu will differ from time to time. Always a new experience. Is not ur regular Korean diner(Old meet New). If u are looking for meats, Butchers will provide their recommendations or suggestions depending on what u want to do with your cut or meat. There is also a Wide selection of Korean “drinks”. If u are around the area or looking for something new to try, I would recommend this diner.
We had the best Korean barbecue outside of Korea! The quality of the ingredients are amazing, straight from their butcher’s counter. Everything was fresh. Service was easy and friendly!
wonderful quality meat at reasonable price and friendly service with a big smile. very happy
Incredibly rude staff

원래 판매하시는 매니저님이 엄청 친절해서 갈때마다 기분좋게 필요한것보다 항상 더 많이 샀었는데요 .오늘은 젊은 여자직원분이 화가 잔뜩난 상태로 판매를 하고 계시네요. 그렇게 화가 나고 짜증이 나있는상태로 몇안되는 고객들 판매를 어떻게 하신다는건지 이해가 안되요. 제품도 점점 구성이 엉성해지던데 다시는 갈 생각없어집니다
로컬마켓에서 해결하고 말지 거기까지 가서 엉망이 서비스 받고싶지도 않습니다.

came here two weeks ago & today again for the BBQ weekend! food quality is consistent, meat is very very good - try the oyster blade & marinated LA galbi. we also really enjoy the grocery store offerings, especially the frozen jjajangmyeon & fritz coffee. a lot of products you can't find elsewhere. manager & cook are helpful & friendly, can't wait to be back!

Limited menu items for dining in. Thus, the saying quality over quantity holds true here.

The beef looks superb. There are many artisanal sauces and pastes to choose from. Good for gifting.

여기 고기 강추! 간만에 입맛에 쏙맞는 한국 스타일의 누린내 안나는 고기집을 찾은 것 같아서 너무 좋아요!! 일단 매장의 깔끔함에 기분이 좋고 고기질에 두번 좋고 뒷편에 있는 막걸리 등등(특히 복순도가..! 덜덜)을 보고 세번 기분 좋아져요~ 안창살하고 갈비살 사서 집에서 요리해 먹었는데 너무 좋았어요! 지인 소개로 왔었는데 앞으로 고기 생각날때마다 자주 올듯 합니다 :) 지평막걸리 맛있게 먹었어요!! 🤗🤗

I brought a Rib and out skirt. The meat here is really good! Most importantly, it does not smell like meat. It is even cheaper than other stores, such as Korean restaurants and restaurants.
I don't know why the review here isn't good!!
I'll go here whenever I want to eat meat dishes and Korean BBQ!!  Above all, the female worker who seemed to be the owner of this store was very kind to us.
I love this place! Good service, consistently good quality variety of meat & their meal kits are top with no MSG. Nice variety of authentic korean products too!
One of the best Korean meat places I’ve ever been to. Brilliant food, impeccable service. 10/10 would recommend going for the weekend grilled meats.

The restaurant have two modes: pick their menu or pick their fresh meat and they will grill for you. Only their pre sliced meats are allowed for grilling. You will have to make payment first before moving in to the restaurant. No complaints on table service. Because the meat is fresh, it won't be fully marinated when served to you in such a short time. Their business model is on the inflexible side. If you picked the grill option, your companions and you are locked in to pay $12 per pax, for grilling and vegetables. Vegetables here is not free flow like typical Korean restaurants. I made a few complaints on the serving size of kimchi and marinated white carrot because I find it ridiculous that I have to share 3 pieces of white carrot between my companion and myself...
The customer service really need to be improved. Especially the Korean lady at the counter, her tone was so rude. It is not worth going back to support.

Contrary to many of the negative reviews here. I actually believe this place deserves more praise. The interior space is nicely curated, the meat quality is excellent and reasonably priced for the amount you get, the kitchen barbecued the meat nicely and the staff are friendly (both at the dining area and shop area). Will definitely come back again!

Walking in to buy some meat, slightly earlier than 11am. The woman at the meat counter was so rude, rushing into the cafe and told us it’s not open in a very impolite way. No smile on her face, terrible service

Get your Korean fix of meats, sauces and DIY meal kits here. Minimalist cafe reminded one of a Korean cafe vibe. Food served features meats and vegs. Ate the Korean beef tartare noodles with perilla oil which was refreshing, light and tasted very clean. Will return to try other favourites like the pork cutlet. There was also Jeju carrot cake which is supposed to be good!

I came here twice and had a good experience with the meats. If you're looking for some good cuts.. do check it out and you'll be quite impressed with it. As for the food, I enjoyed the spicy Korean bimbap which unfortunately I did not manage to take a photo as I ate it too quickly. Overall I would come to this place again... perhaps with more people so I can try their other Korean dishes.

Best way to describe this place is to say it’s the Korean version of Culina at Dempsey. It has a butchery and a small but higher end selection of Korean groceries. The food they serve, while limited in selection, are all done with premium ingredients and well executed. the staff are also very attentive and extremely helpful. Browse their menu online before heading down and you won’t be disappointed.

Location is kinda hard to access.
But it’s near to havelock mrt (Not yet open)
The old school Duroc pork cutlet is really good. Beef bulgogi & spicy jeyuk is average taste, comes without rice so you gotta order it separately. Yukke perilla oil noodle is savoury yet clean taste & the coldness of noodle made it nicer. Yukke bibimbap is not bad but i prefer the noodle. Candy tomato is very small portion. Price is a little expensive overall but it’s a quiet place so it’s a very good place to hang out.

A very pleasant dining experience where we get to choose the meat and have it cooked for us on the spot. Staff were very friendly and helpful in recommending the different cuts of meat.
The meat were seasoned with just salt and pepper and bbq-ed to perfect doneness.
It can feel as though the restaurant is on the pricey side but with the quality of food/meat served, it's definitely worth the price.
A new kbbq dining experience whereby the cooking is all done by the staff in the kitchen while we just sit and wait to be served.
The restaurant had a really good ambience and definitely made the dining experience more enjoyable.
